<refentry xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:db="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" version="5.0-subset Scilab" xml:lang="en" xml:id="ind2rgb"><info><pubdate>August, 2007</pubdate></info><refnamediv><refname>ind2rgb</refname><refpurpose>convert indexed image to true color image  </refpurpose></refnamediv>
  
  
  
  
  
  <refsynopsisdiv><title>Calling Sequence</title><synopsis>rgb = ind2rgb(ind,cmap)</synopsis></refsynopsisdiv>
  <refsection><title>Parameters</title>
 <variablelist>
  <varlistentry>
  <term>rgb</term>
  <listitem>
    MxNx3 true color image in the 0-1 range
  </listitem> 
  </varlistentry>
  <varlistentry>
  <term>ind  </term>
  <listitem>
    MxN indexed image, integer matrix
  </listitem> 
  </varlistentry>
 <varlistentry>
  <term>cmap  </term>
  <listitem>
    color map
  </listitem> 
  </varlistentry>
   </variablelist>
  </refsection>
  <refsection><title>Description</title>
  <para>
  ind2rgb utility function converts an indexed image to true color image for pseudo color visualization.
  </para>
  </refsection>
  <refsection><title>Examples</title><programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
  a=[1:0.05:16];
  b=int32(a'*a);
  cmap=jetcolormap(256);
  c=ind2rgb(b,cmap);
  imshow(c);
 ]]></programlisting></refsection>

